data.enText: a government official who is the representative of his or her country in a foreign city

tr: a diplomat appointed by a government to protect its commercial interests and help its citizens in a foreign country

value.def: A consul is an official who is sent by his or her government to live in a foreign city in order to look after all the people there that belong to his or her own country.

example.ex: The British Consul in Zurich has confirmed that a British man was among the people killed.
example.tran: 英国驻苏黎世领事证实被害人中有一名英国籍男子。

trans: 总领事（指最高级别的领事）
